org.orgName: District Court of the Territory of Washington Spokane County

body.p: Territory of Washington, County of Spokane. SS.
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Spokane Falls.
In the matter of the application of B. Norman for a writ of Habeas Corpus.
To J.F. Warren, Chief of Police, City of Spokane Falls.

In the name of the United States, you are hereby commanded that you have the body of B. Norman by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonmrnt and detention, by whatever name the said B. Norman shall be called or charged, before Hon. George Turner, Judge of the District Court of the Fourth Judicial District of the Territory of Washington, at the Court House in the city of Spokane Falls, said county and Territory, on Saturday, February 25, 1888, at ten o'clock in the forenoon of said day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered of him the said B. Norman, and have you then and there this writ with your return thereon.
Witness the HON. GEORGE TURNER, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the seal thereof affixed, this 24th day of February, 1888.

Territory of Washington County of } SS Spokane I hereby certify by virtue of the within writ i now have in custody and return in to court The within named defendant B. Norman as by directed by the within writ
Filed this the 25th day of Feb, 1888 J.F. Warren Chief Police
In the matter of the application of B. Norman for a writ of habeas corpus
